The large central town square in Gyumri, Armenia. It is bordered by the Abovyan street from the west, Gai street from the north, Shahumyan street from the east and Vahan Cheraz street from the south. It has a rectangular shape (280 by 140 meters).
The square was known as the May Uprising Square, named after the failed Bolshevik uprising against the Dashnak government of the First Republic of Armenia in May 1920. The square was opened during the 1930s under the Soviet rule, based on the original plan of Alexander Tamanian and the revised plan of D. Chislian.

This is an amazing experience for anyone that comes out here. I highly recommend this at such a reasonable price. You can get tickets at the visitor's center. The tour guide was friendly and knowledgeable. We were encouraged to ask as many questions as we wanted. It was a fun experience. The horses were also amazing.

This place is awesome. I have the opportunity to be one of the sleigh guides and see what really goes on out here. Getting up close and personal with these Elk is truly an incredible experience. These animals are wild and you get to see them in their natural winter environment. It is a must for anyone coming to the Jackson Hole area. Dress warm and come on over. you are in for a ride of a lifetime.

If you’re going to be in Jackson Hole, take a sleigh ride at the Elk Refuge. It’s a one of a kind experience. The location is beautiful, the tour guides are very knowledgeable, and the elk are fascinating. The sleigh allows you to get unbelievably close to these incredible animals. The proceeds of the ride go directly to the Elk Refuge and its works. It is certainly worth a visit!

We had an amazing time.  Our hostess was very knowledgeable, nice and fun. The information center was fun and educational as well. They had multiple live, wild birds on display including an owl and a bald eagle. Soo fun for all ages!

Took 1 day off from skiing, and absolutely loved the elk refuge and sleigh ride tour. $25 for the full deal including the sleigh ride out to the elk, so white the deal!! Our tour guide was incredibly knowledgeable. Lots of volunteers who are very passionate. Also saw a bald eagle and coyotes. 

If you have time after or before, go to kellys hot springs ~20 minutes away where buffalo and other wildlife congregate.

Went by at 10 til 6:00 and the place was closed...a  store should stick to its posted hours.

In response to the business owner, the reason for my low rating is clear, so readers may weigh it accordingly.  Like many of the galleries in the area we found yours closed on multiple occasions, and some others also inconsistently with their posted hours (and the notice of an "installation" was not informative); and we were quite frustrated as our time in the area was limited.  By contrast, one gallery was open each time we went by, and we ended up purchasing a piece of artwork there.  This review  simply reflected our experience, as do the other reviews I have posted, whether positive or negative.
Great gallery with a friendly staff!  The art is fantastic!  We go there every summer to see what's new and sometimes find a great piece for our house.

My late husband and I happened into RARE when we spent the night in Jackson Hole.  We were so taken with the choices of artwork and the style of their gallery; both were very contemporary. We bought a piece by C Spielman of a bison and it brings back such wonderful memories.
Best gallery in Jackson and right on Town Square.  The owners Rick and Hollee are awesome. Check it out!
Such a unique experience, not stuffy like other art galleries are and the people that worked there were so nice and helpful to answer my questions. Such a hidden gem!
This setting cannot be beat. After a demanding hike or climb, their comfort food at the buffet is much appreciated. Kind of kitschy but I love this place.

Went here for breakfast on a Sunday morning. The menu is very limited so don’t expect a lot of options. The food takes quite a long time, though it is very good. Coffee and hot cocoa have unlimited refills. Views of the mountains are great. Plenty of seating.
I had a calzone one day that was great and a slice of pizza with a side Greek salad my second visit that was delicious
Bratwurst on the deck, good. Thanks Dornan's.

One of the best experience I had at Jackson Hole / Grand Teton is this place. It was unfortunate there were smoke looming in the area at the time we were there, but the view was still spectacular with food equally good. Meats and the sides both delicious. The only downside was my stomach. I didn't have enough room for dessert and their hot cocoa

This place has a warm, cabin feel inside and a beautiful dining area. The service is incredible, and they run this place like a well-oiled machine! On top of it, the food is great. Not so many vegetarian options, but they're happy to accommodate dietary needs. The chocolate souffle for dessert is a must!

The food was amazing and can't wait to visit again! We were seated right away after getting there (we had reservations of course). The hostess took our coats and bags from shopping to the back so we didn't have to lug it with us to our table. The restaurant was pretty crowded and they have a good amount of tables in there. The reason we only gave 4 stars is our waitress was rushing and not very outgoing. She could have been having a bad night, but with a place like this you expect great service.

Tasty!  I am vegetarian, which seemed to offend the waitress.  Strange.  She said, twice, “oh, so you are eating light tonight”.  I guess since I didn’t order the Tenderloin she thought her tip was going to suffer.  Anyway, what I ate was delicious!  The yams, roasted cauliflower & the mushroom dish.  The Caesar salad was especially yummy!   Hopefully the server was pleased with her tip.

I eat out quite a bit, so it's not that common that I have a "wow" meal, but I had one at the Snake River Grill. I had the lobster chowder which was delicious, while my wife had the winter greens salad. Also, delicious. We both had the New York strip. The New York is my favorite cut of steak, and this was the best I've had. Cooked to perfection. A chocolate souffle for dessert. The service was great. Just a really great evening. Dying to go back. I was really impressed with how reasonably priced it was for Jackson.

Snotty and condescending staff.   If that's your jam, this place is for you.   If you have no time for pretentious behaviour...move along.

To elaborate:. It was clear they didn't want us there at the restaurant.   See Date Night scene at Claw ("You're welcome").
Excellent Thai food. Fast and friendly service. We had the Pineapple fried rice,  Pad Thai and Red Curry. All were delicious and large portions. Egg Rolls were great too. Highly recommended!
Very authentic and delicious! We eat here every time we're in Jackson. Remember to bring your own booze!

This place is honestly a hidden gem here ! The place is very unassuming and quaint, nothing fancy but the food was excellent ! I eat quite a bit of Thai food and this was definitely better than many I've had! Had the mussuman , the panang salmon, the coconut milk soup, and chicken satay. The peanut sauce is amazing .I was just eating what was left with a spoon! The Thai tea was definitely one of the better ones I've had as well. Creamy, smooth and not sickeningly sweet  If I'm back in jackson Wyoming I'm coming back!!! The food was served quite fast and the server was kind and attentive as well. They don't have beer but you can bring your own! Which is pretty cool I think.
Smelled funky inside but you expect a Thai place to smell like fish sauce right? The food was extremely good and the portion size of the curry was massive! The Green Curry is perfect.
Good, spicy food and pleasant staff.  The dumplings we're different, but delicious, like a meatloaf.
Fun night! We loved all of it. The drinks were perfect and the waiter tolerated us! Lol. Great french onion soup and the bread! Yum.
The people were amazing... friendly, happy, fun, and totally professional and very good at thier jobs! Food...amazing!
Outstanding food! Great service!

We went to Rendezvous Bistro today. It was pretty busy, but our table was ready fast. First we ordered couple cocktails, which were great , then  for appetizers we had  Fried Calamari and Beef Tacos. Calamari were really good and beef taco was just okay (little dry). We’ve been waiting pretty long for entree’s (about 40 min after appetizers). We got our Veal Marsala and Steak Frites. I ordered steak well done, but it was really BURNED and tasted so bitter and dry.  Steak comes with house-made fries, but it doesn’t taste good either. Fries is so thin. Veal Marsala tasted better, but still nothing special. Now it’s off season in Jackson and they have great deal $2 for second entree, so this made our check look much better. Prices are normal. $13-$14 for each appetizer, steak is $34 and $33 for Veal Marsala. Service was okay. After all, we got not so good impression about this place.

The Rendezvous Bistro is always a safe bet for good food at reasonable prices,  at least by Jackson standards.  The scallops are great, as is the fried chicken.  Desserts are standard fare, unfortunately nothing that really stands out. If the building looks familiar to those who come from a city, it should because it is in a former Denny's.

Trio has a great atmosphere with an awesome staff. We came in for the New Years preset menu which sounded divine! Our first courses were great, however our steak came out over cooked and we were quite bummed. Fortunately the chef came by and asked us how our experience was, and he immediately sent out a new perfectly cooked steak and won us over! The food really is incredible and the chefs do a great job. We will be back and greatly appreciate the customer service!

Though the portions seemed small, the food was very good at Trio. Our server forgot about us a few times (neglecting to bring drinks or check in about the meal), but she was very friendly and knowledgeable. Probably just overworked. The atmosphere was nice, too, though it was exceptionally loud.
Had the fish special. It was great. Grouper asparagus and potatoes. The fish was crisp on the outside and soft on the inside.

We tried this place because the chef of a restaurant in Raleigh, NC we love recommended it. The food was absolutely delicious and the hostess/host were so welcoming and kind. Unfortunately, we had a rude waiter who acted like we were inconveniencing him every time we ordered. He was very short and made a snide comment after we asked for a recommendation on an appetizer and we went for the opposite of his choice. We didn’t pick his recommendation bc he didn’t seem enthused or that he cared what we ordered. This restaurant is in my top 3 favorites while staying in Jackson; just unfortunate we had a negative encounter with a server.
Good food, reasonable price, and it's Jackson hole.

What a headache!  I purchased two glass figurines as gifts only to discover when I returned to my hotel room that they were full of several small chips.  I went back the next morning.  Unfortunately, the store does not do returns, which is a shame since they were selling damaged products.  I could not exchange them for the same item because all the figurines they had left were chipped, too.  So I had to find other items to make up the exchange.  I settled on a shirt and pen.  The cashiers working there are very young women who speak very softly and quietly and are lacking in customer service skills.  It doesn't help that music is blaring loudly all of the time.  It took  30 minutes for these cashiers to do the math and figure out the exchange and process it on their computers/registers.  It shouldn't have been that complicated.  I had to get out my phone calculator to help. It was frustrating to spend all that time doing a store exchange that should have been relatively simple rather than being out enjoying the beautiful sites.

Um this is a souvenir store. The mangy moose bar is something totally different. As a souvenir shop though for our lovely town Great Prices in here. Peruse the goods to fine owl oven mitts and dog magnets. It has a nice selection of tshirts and stuff too.
Awesome stuff. Lots of it too. Cool place... Can't wait to go back.
If you Mike moose, and you like emporiums, you will absolutely love this place.
Good tourist store

Gorgeous building! I didn't have any unexpected fees for anything. The Florida Theatre website informs that there are parking garages and gives you the prices/ price ranges and their distance from the theatre for each one. We went to see Aaron Lewis, one of my all time favorite artists! The show was amazing, except everyone sitting in the rows in front of us (all 49 rows) wouldn't stay seated. They kept getting up and down, usually 5 or more people would leave a row to get a drink, they'd come back, then another group of 4 would get up and all leave to get their drinks...it was an on going thing without a break from start to finish. And you know when one person has to leave a row, then everyone else in that row needs to stand up to let them out. This made for my experience a little unpleasant. I couldn't enjoy or even see most of the show. It's not the venues fault, but it is something that may need to be fixed eventually. Maybe getting servers...honestly, anything to help keep the guests in their seats would make it an even better experience. I enjoyed how fast they got everyone in, even while wanding all guest and their purses. The guests constantly getting up and standing in front, without a care in the world was my only bad thing to say.

Beautiful venue. The seating is great and even sitting all the way in the back you still get a great view of the stage. Hosts some very very entertaining acts here. I saw Ghost perform at this venue and it was hands down one of the greatest shows I've ever seen in my life. Perfect atmosphere. Great acoustics.

1st of all the theater itself is an amazing piece of artwork all by itself. The inside of the building is absolutely beautiful! To be as old of a building it is, it remains to be in pretty good shape showing off all the beautiful architecture work put into this place. It's just unreal! Last night, my wife and I were here for a concert featuring, Dennis DeYoung and the music of Styx and "Night Ranger!" Yeah, it's only been 35 years since I've seen these guys. And 35 years later you know what, they still rock the house like they own it. Both shows were awesome!

Fantastic venue! The staff is awesome. My wife lost her phone. They were so courteous and nice as to find it and hold it for us on lost and found. Such honesty is rare these days. Especially at concerts and other entertainment venues. Thank you Kathleen for being so awesome!

What a great theatre. It was a little tricky to find but parking was easy. The theatre is absolutely beautiful and recreated to mimic theatres of old with gold paint and carvings and stained glass windows. Acoustics were outstanding. Attendants were efficient and knowledgeable. It was a wonderful experience and we will certainly return for other shows.
Great place to take photos. Very pretty at night. Love seeing the bridge raise for boaters to pass.
Gentle evening riverfront stroll, photo taken by the Hyatt Regency.
Nice historic bridge.
I saw two kids just laying in the walkway making out. It was disgusting. I bet they are in love. Gross. They should have just jumped off.
An immediate favorite

Great "old style" movie theater. Food selections were numerous, fairly quick, and of good quality. The bathrooms were clean, the theater had some sticky areas on tables, but pretty clean, overall. Friendly staff. Nice diversion from the chain theaters.

One of the best if not the best theaters to go to in Jacksonville Fl. They have comfortable seats, great sound, and great food. Local draft beers, and wine. You can even bring your own bottle of wine(small corking fee). I recommend there pizza, paninis, and the best popcorn in town. Get there 20 minutes early so you can eat, drink, and pick out a great seat. Enjoy.
A great venue to watch a movie! Pizza is delicious, the beer ice cold, and the seats very comfortable. I LOVE THIS THEATRE!!!!
I used to live really close to this movie theater. It is the best in town by a landslide. This is an awesome spot for a date night. End the night with a Starbucks and walk around the square

San Marco Theatre is a family staple for first run films. We are thrilled to order beverages and hot foods in a comfortable theater environment. Eclectic films are no stranger here and the staff make this theater a welcome retreat. We keep San Marco Theater’s schedule in our smartphone and the posted show times are reliable. There is handicap access and ample parking. Movie prices are discounted for students. I recommend you experience San Marco Theater.

The Jacksonville Karpeles Manuscript Library Museum’s primary mission is the preservation and educational presentation of the writings of great authors, scientists, composers, philosophers, statesmen, sovereigns, and leaders, from all periods in world history. 

The Museum strives to promote education and literacy within Jacksonville, with an emphasis on the under-served neighborhoods and constituents. The Jacksonville Karpeles is one of nine Karpeles Museums around the country and the museum founders are committed to providing each of these communities free access to original manuscript exhibits. Collections and documents rotate.  Sometimes local artists display their art collections as well.
It's not a large museum, can probably read through everything thoroughly in 30 min, maybe 1 hour max if you like to go through museums slowly. 5 stars since it's free and they have interesting stuff.

Great venue! I have attended weddings, memorial services, fundraisers, concerts, and art shows at Karpeles. It has some amazing historic documents in its permanent collection as well as many wonderful letters and documents that come through on tour.

A private museum, one of the older buildings in downtown Jacksonville that features unique (to 1920's) architectural details and it is FREE to the public!  Collections/documents are rotated on a set schedule.  Sometimes local artists display their art collections as well.  The main auditorium has some resemblance to a theater, with a stage and a balcony, but main floor is an open flex space.  The building can be rented by hour.

A fascinating place displaying documents from Samual B. Morse relating to his telegraph. Very much a hidden gem. It does not take long and you may have the place to yourself. You will see something very rare and likely learn a thing or two!

It is a beautiful place. Roomy. Very exquisitely setup. There was a lot of people for the event I was there for but it was not stuffy or cold. The temperature was perfect. The lighting was awesome. The waitstaff was quick & friendly as well non- intrusive. It was just a very welcoming and comfortable atmosphere.

We brought our students for a field trip. The staff was so accommodating, helpful and patient. They really went out of their way for the children! Their resources and art centers were engaging. We'd love to come back for another visit!
It was very beautifully decorated.  As having an event and filled with people, the temperature was perfect. The finger foods and drinks were delicious. The wait staff was polite and friendly.

Always a pleasure when I visit the museum to see the creative and thought provoking works presented by the local and visiting national artist. Well clean and well maintained and never crowded even on the busiest nights due to proper crowd/ visitor control. Worth a visit to view some very interesting and beautiful pieces of art.
Only ate here. Good food and short wait. Parking in a ramp in next block. Eclectic food. Good prices.

It’s a decent museum. Nothing spectacular. The staff could have been more welcoming. Many(many!)of the exhibits weren’t even working and no one was trying to fix it. So we were basically walking around and staring at activities. The planetarium show(tour of the solar system) was nice. Seemed a bit fake and the live narrator wasn’t very interesting (although you can tell he was doing his best). The seats and room were nice but it smelled muggy(like carpets and seats need to be cleaned). I was disappointed because I wanted my kids to enjoy more interactive learning activities and there wasn’t much especially because many were broken. The MOSH seems awesome from the outside but inside...not so great.

Read that this was one of the best museums in Jacksonville and decided to check it out. I did not realize until after buying my ticket that the museum is probably more suited towards children with just enough stuff to keep an adult entertained. If you have children, this would be a great place to take them. Still worth it as an adult but a lot of stuff for younger children.

We had family in for Thanksgiving so we decided to go to MOSH on Black Friday. I was unsure of what to expect having never been here before and reading decidedly mixed reviews. From the Hurricane Force Winds simulator, to the planetarium, to the interactive learning exhibits about the body and sea animals, MOSH has fun for all ages. EVERYONE was smiling and laughing, from my 8 year old to my 60 year old mother! It is a unique learning experience centered around hands on gathering of information, stimulation of the senses, and hilarious chances for facebook worthy pictures. Totally worth the overpriced tickets.
Great fun! Lots to learn. I think the adults had the most fun this time! We will definitely be back.

The science of the earth is amazing to see all the theories. A family could spend all day here and not be able to see and participate in all the fun. So maybe come early, take a break for a meal and then explore the rest of the place or just plan two visits to be able to enjoy each educational exhibit fully. Most of the exhibits are interactive and fun for all ages.

It is a beautiful place. Roomy. Very exquisitely setup. There was a lot of people for the event I was there for but it was not stuffy or cold. The temperature was perfect. The lighting was awesome. The waitstaff was quick & friendly as well non- intrusive. It was just a very welcoming and comfortable atmosphere.

We brought our students for a field trip. The staff was so accommodating, helpful and patient. They really went out of their way for the children! Their resources and art centers were engaging. We'd love to come back for another visit!
It was very beautifully decorated.  As having an event and filled with people, the temperature was perfect. The finger foods and drinks were delicious. The wait staff was polite and friendly.

Always a pleasure when I visit the museum to see the creative and thought provoking works presented by the local and visiting national artist. Well clean and well maintained and never crowded even on the busiest nights due to proper crowd/ visitor control. Worth a visit to view some very interesting and beautiful pieces of art.
Only ate here. Good food and short wait. Parking in a ramp in next block. Eclectic food. Good prices.
Love this beautiful park. Nice bathrooms. Nice neighborhood.
Always nice for our class reunion picnic.   Bathrooms are always very clean, as well. 👍
Lots of fun! The historical society is located in the center building in the center of the park.

Memorial Park is the heart of Claremont. Major events happen here from 5k races to the whole 4th of July extravaganza. Every day it's a pleasant park. Always clean.
4th of July in Claremont is a throwback to a simpler time. Memorial park is the staging grounds for the parade. There are booths from all the local vendors and a pancake breakfast. Kids and adults can ride their bikes or scooters or roller skates or whatever in the parade.  Always free and fun.
In the summer, the city fills the splash pool for toddlers to cool off in a safe shallow fountain.
It's a great place to grab a sandwich from Wolfes and have a picnic.
Fun place to bring the kids and grandkids for a fun day in the natural world of parks😎
Awesome place for a great sunrise walk or even a sundown walk. My family and I have even went at 1 a.m. and it was still great. Well lit and always feel safe there.
Very peaceful place to spend time with family, alone, or get a nice walk/jog. There are plenty of spots to take nice picture's because of the scenery. One of my favorite locations.

Beautiful view and well maintained walk. Great place to go walking, mornings, evenings or anytime. Open to bicycle use also. The breeze is usually pretty nice and it's a good place to view fireworks on the holidays that have them. Parking can be a little hard to find.
Very nice, quiet walk on the river. The path under the Main St Bridge is very cool. It drops down near level with the waterline and gives a great view of the north bank.

Ok, so its unlikely to be on a typical European holiday makers 'must see' list - but if you're in the area - and the Jax beaches, A1A drive, Amelia Island and St. Augustine area is great for scenery, nature trails, cycling, fishing and even (rare in the US) historical sites - then the Jacksonville river-walk is worth a try. They've obviously spent a lot of money rejuvenating the north & south riverbanks and they look great though there's some hurricane damage still to fix. We were even lucky enough to see dolphins hunting between the bridges. The Saturday artist market and ample free parking make it the best day to visit.

Love this place.  This is the second time I've been there in the last six years, all the way from Canada would have been nice to see inside the main house this time. The roadway in needs to be gravel or paved or graded it's horrid other than that lovely
First visit. Nice place to spend the day to learn some historical facts. They also allow you to go fishing in the back of the facility.

All of the Park Rangers were very knowledgeable and very friendly. The plantation is very well preserved. We will be returning in the fall for harvest day to continue our education on the history of this place. Also planning on booking a guided tour next time as well. Vey educational for the whole family.

There are 2 roads that lead to the Plantation.Go towards the gold club (right road). That one is paved most of the way. The road on the left where the arrow directs you to is a dirt road with lots of potholes for over 2 miles. The plantation and slaves quarters were interesting to see. The house was closed and there wasn't a ranger available for seeing inside the house. Grounds are well maintained. You can go into the barn and kitchen area. Worth the stop.

I just took my son on a scout hike here, and it was very interesting to learn about the history of the plantation while we hiked the trails. It is very well kept, and the trail by the water makes a spectacular spot to take pictures with nature.

Our food was delicious as always. Bread pudding , scallops and pasta and the grilled chicken sandwich. Happy hour is always wonderful as well and this evening was too. Yet our server was friendly but not attentive. Friday evening we were able to pull right into a spot on their lot. We were seated in the main dining room which is nicely decorated. We chose starters of calamari and a 3 cheese plate. The calamari was non traditional and just excellent! Service was attentive. Entrees were the scallops and the lamb shank

If I recall Katie was our server. The atmosphere and service was spot on. The food was great and I enjoyed my dinner with friends. Each meal was prepared per our own liking, temperatures were exactly what we wanted. The drinks were perfect although I must admit the Russian Mule was great but as the first time trying it the ginger beer made my throat irritated, not on the fault of drink but just my experience
Fantastic place with a full craft cocktail bar! Stopped here on my way through town. I asked for a drink not on the menu and the friendly bartender made it any way. Great food too! Highly recommend!

We enjoyed a variety of small plates prior to attending the concert. Loved the Tuna, Duck and mussels/clams would pass on the shrimp lollipops because I am not a big fan of shrimp cakes. Venue, food, service and an outside seat were the bee’s knees! Returned after the concert for a night cap. Late night service was excellent with a friendly, knowledgeable bartender. I recommend making a reservation. The place is cool and therefore packed!

Great downtown culinary destination. We stopped in for appetizers. Ended up ordering three, shared them, then ordered the Chocolate ganache cake. What a great place! Service was fantastic, manager stopped by our table, and the ambiance with light jazz, recessed lighting, highly recommend. Planning on bringing friends for our next visit

The people are so nice, and they have a great variety of books of all kinds and movies and series and episodes. I also liked that they had High School girls and boys working there to earn a living and learning how to make money. Overall the parking would probably suck during the week, but the weekend are great is for parking as long as there are no events going on overall I give them five stars to thumbs up

Awesome downtown spot to grab coffee, a sweet treat, or a proper breakfast/lunch and of course a book to accompany your meal, naturally. Outdoor seating is nice, right along the sidewalk, and the vantage point actually makes it feel like you’re in a real city! Cafe inside is cozy. Staff is friendly. Only issue I can find is the presence of homeless people. They keep to themselves for the most part but the park across the street attracts a lot of them so just be aware. This is a nice addition to the bookstore of theirs south of downtown since that one is without a cafe. And with the holidays around the corner it’s quite festive!

It is a wonderful place to go if you have found a book you love and want to purchase. They have everything including first editions. There is also a deli where you can get a cup of coffee or a sandwich. I LOVE the atmosphere which is like an old fashioned bookstore that's been there for a hundred years.

A pretty interesting spot in downtown Jax. They have a very diverse collection of books and they also offer a variety of food items and beverages. You can simply buy a book and start reading it right away while you’re sipping on your coffee. 
That said, there are a few things I wish they could improve; one is their WiFi service that is (or at least used to be) unreliable and the other is the crowd you get in the cafe area. The second one I think is a side effect of being located around the Hemming park and honestly the cafe owners are doing their best to make the situation better. The lady in the book shop always looks out for the real customers and don’t let anyone disturb them to the best of her ability.
Amazing amount of books upstairs and down. Amazingly organized so you can find what you are looking for. I'm impressed!

A quiet Cafe that is tucked away by Hemming Park. Fresh sandwiches can be enjoyed here. Hard to park here and it's not open for dinner or on the weekends, but that is more of a symptom of downtown Jacksonville.

The food is delicious, I highly recommend the quiche and the pulled cream of chicken soup. I have tried their sandwiches and those are delicious, as well. Great spot for lunch in downtown Jacksonville.
Great vegan options. Super yummy

Nice place, not the greatest hours.
Had a crouque monsier sandwich, was decent, i ask if they could make it a madam, was told no by the chef, all they would've needed is to add a sunny side up egg on top.
I dont think I'll be going back, especially with Chamberlains next door.
Cashier was a delight though
Food is good, but I thought it was a Cat cafe. :( DissapDissap there are no cats

Boyfriend and I were visiting & when we first arrived host acted like we weren’t welcomed. Then we had a server who drops our drinks off and had another server pick up the table.After all of this we ended up with Drew. Literally the best service I ever received. He knew everything about the menu plus more. He made our first experience at Ruth Chris our best experience. He was super friendly and made sure everything was perfect! Definitely will be back to sit with him.

My wife surprised me here for my birthday.   From the time we arrived we were greeted and treated with a personal touch. 

The food was absolutely amazing.  Our server "Will" seemed like a friend more than a server.  Will was very knowledgeable about all aspects of the menu's they offer.  Not too mention, he offered suggestions according to our palette.

Every moment of our experience at Ruth's was memorable.  The view, the food/ drink, the service, and the atmosphere is all 5 star!

Looking forward to my next visit.

That  was my first time ever going there and it WILL NOT be my last. The stuffed chicken was AMAZING! The sweet potato casserole tasted like a dream! I've never had anything so delicious. The lobster Mac and cheese was seasoned to perfection. Even the mash potatoes were delicious. It is worth every cent spent.

Fancy Birthday Dinner.  It was an excellent time.  I has to go for the 40 oz Tomahawk Steak, that was savory and sizzling on a 500 degree plate. I ate most of it, and brought my appetite.  The lobster mac and cheese was perfectly paired with my steak, and very cheesy deliciousness.  My Husband chose the stuffed chicken and it was moist and juicy.  The Calamari was sweet paired nicely with my sweet Moscato wine. 1st time at Ruth Chris and we will definitely be back for our Anniversary in June.  To top it off they brought me a birthday dessert, salted caramel cheesecake, that was excellent.

Ruth's Chris Steak House is an institution when it comes to fine dining.  This is where you go for all the important and milestone celebrations. I really shouldn't say that....Frank and I go there three or four times a year.
I'm not a steak eater, as I have said before, but even I can tell that the steaks at Ruth's Chris are in a catagory all their own.  The steaks are aged to perfection, then they are seared over a flame,
from that point they are plated and finished cooking and properly rested before being placed in front of you.....and if you don't start salivating immediately I would be very surprised!
When you order sides they are meant to be shared.  So if you go in as a couple, two sides will be more than enough.  Ruth's Chris offers a good selection of sides.  I will tell you that if you like Sweet Potatoes, make sure you order the Sweet Potato Casserole....I have seen people order it for dessert!  Yes, it's that good!!!  They don't always offer Onion Rings, but if they do have them on the menu, they are worth ordering as well.
When you call to make reservations make sure you let them know if it's for a celebration.  Birthdays and Anniversaries are always treated special if they know ahead of time.  Your table will be decorated and after your meal they offer a free dessert.  
This is a pricey restaurant, be prepared to drop between $100-150 for two people. For a special dinner out, I know you won't be disappointed.
If you live in Jacksonville go right now!!   What a fantastic place.  Food and service we're unbelievable.  Can't wait to go back and try more tapas.

This restaurant is a hidden gem in Jacksonville...a perfect Bourdain-like experience, tucked away in a small space on Stockton Street. This cozy spot is like being transported to another place far away from the city. The food is simply exquisite. Truly, every dish is high level gourmet meets comfort food. My husband and I cherish this little space and actually drive from the beach to experience it when we can.
Loved the food. The flavors were amazing although I was a little disappointed that the portions were so small.

This is my husband’s and my favorite restaurant in Jacksonville. Mushroom Sevilla, couscous salad, curry cauliflower and Brussels sprouts are just some of the must-haves. And even though you’ll be stuffed, the bread pudding is a must as well. Fun atmosphere and always fun music playing.

Worst dining experience in Jacksonville so far! I’ve been to many tapas style places before and love the idea so decided to give this place a shot. Upon arriving to the restaurant, the first surprise was that the menu was nothing like the menu that we saw online - different dishes with steeper prices. Boyfriend and I ordered two small plates for starters - the pear and date dish and the meatball dish. We were shocked when the plates came out and there were literally like 4 meatballs? The pear dish was so small we literally had a bite each. The concept of tapas is to share and that was Barely enough food for one person to sample. The food tasted great but That sad appetizer and what must have been a 3 oz glass of wine cost us around $40. We ended up going to burrito gallery after because we were both still starving. Very disappointed. Save your money and go somewhere else.

I forgot what I had, but it started with a C and it had crab in it. Cousset maybe? It was amazing. I wish I could remember the name of our waiter, but he was very accommodating. The food is delicious and the service if prompt. I had the meatloaf sandwich which was exquisitely seasoned, best meatloaf I've ever had. The mimosas are also great, they are generous with their champagne but they are a bit pricey. The food is fairly priced.

Not only is this restaurant one of my favorite places to dine, I LOVE that I can reserve the side room for private events. The staff is always so attentive, and the food is always top notch. I could live in the dessert case!

I loved this place! It was delicious! I had the Grilled turkey burger. While it's definitely not a traditional burger to common standards, it was very good. Service was great as well. Possibly the most serene sight amidst the chaos of Jaipur is the beautiful Jal Mahal Jaipur, the Water Palace. This low-rise symmetrical palace, that once was a shooting lodge for the Maharajah, appears to float in the centre of Sagar Lake. The light sand coloured stone walls of the Jal Mahal Jaipur are at a stark contrast to the deep blue of the waters of the lake, while from the innards of the palace lush foliage sprouts.

This majestic scene makes the Jal Mahal Jaipur’s most photographed (and photograph friendly) monument but unfortunately exploration of the actual palace is off limits to the majority of visitors as it is to be transformed into an ultra exclusive restaurant.

Granted, the masks are interesting and high quality, but they are completely decontextualized with cryptic captions an little explanation tying anything together.

There is one table showing the evolution of money that was nice. 

It's one of the few times I wished there was a museum gift shop with some books.

You can get the information from the museum's guide about the history of proclamation. From the World War II until the proclamation. The staff are very friendly and there is a car park too. If you want to pray there are also a mosque for the muslim and church for the christian near this building. You can do a prayer at the Sunda Kelapa mosque for the muslim. Mesjid Istiqlal is a famous mosque in Jakarta. The mosque is so huge that it can accommodate as many as 120,000 people making it the biggest mosque in South East Asia. The mosque is an architectural delight, and resonates peace when one goes inside. It serves as the praying place for the muslims of the country but it is visited by everyone from all walks of life.

It's the largest mosque in South East Asia and in Jakarta..
No entry fees for this.
It's location is very prime in central Jakarta and is very close to Monas and Merdeka Square.
Just opposite to it is the Jakarta Cathedral..
It's huge in size.. They have big parking facility available but it's crowded most of the time specially in on weekends so keep that in mind.
Carry a polythene along to keep your footwears in it else there would be people just outside selling it to them.
There is a counter where u can deposit your shoes if you are a local and Muslim. In case your are a tourist from other country, then just right to the counter is an information desk sort where u can enter your details in the register.. Also, you will be required to put your shoes in the guest room and not the usual place.
If you are not Muslim, then you will not be allowed to go to first floor of the mosque. You can go on the second floor and click photographs.
Make sure you are well dressed and covered when u arrive here (both men and women) else they provide clothes to cover you up.
The architecture is world class and good place for praying.. 
Overall nice place and worth visiting once

The ice creams are really great, aesthetics aside. It has an affordable price range for people to hang around friends and family while eating ice cream!

Old ice cream joint. But the ice cream taste is unforgettable, loved by all ages. Their specialty is the nougat ice cream, light green colored, with the crushed nuts as the topping. No air con, some people who can't stand the heat, would rather eat the ice cream in their own car in the parking lot.

Tasted nostalgic, however not my really my fave compared to modern ice cream. The place is humid and crowded, gotta move fast if you want to have a seat. Despite all that, I still coming here whenever I have guests from outside Jakarta. It's definitely a must visit place if you love history or if you want to see and feel the "old Jakarta". Cross Fit Jolly Roger was a great box that I plan on returning to whenever I’m in the area. The management/trainers at the facility are knowledgeable and personable. The facility is clean and well equipped. Great box for a great workout!

I started this journey over 2 years ago and I'm SO incredibly thankful that I chose to take it with CrossFit Jolly Roger! I look forward to going in every time and I always feel amazing when I leave - like I've really accomplished something. And I believe that is because of the culture and atmosphere that has been cultivated with the members and the coaches. I absolutely LOVE the coaches at CFJR. Each one brings a different style and are diligent in watching athletes to ensure proper form, which is super important to me. I don't feel like a number or means to an end. I feel like part of the family! I encourage and recommend you check out CF Jolly Roger if you're even the slightest bit interested in giving CrossFit a try.

They were great hosts when I needed to do a last minute drop in. Everyone was in good spirits and the class I was working out with was very supportive of each other and that is something that I love to see. I loved the atmosphere and I felt like I fit in as soon as I walked in there. If you’re looking to have a great community around you and motivate you, I suggest CrossFit Jolly Roger. Thank you again, guys!

I love the atmosphere here at CrossFit Jolly Roger! Everyone pushes themselves to become better everyday and no one has complaints. Our programming is top notch. You won’t find a better gym to get the best experience and be in the best shape of your life. Come see us coaches and let us show you why we are the best around!
We've been to this restaurant numerous times over the past 20 years. Tonight our chef was awesome. He changed his cooking style, we had a great time. Give him a high 5.

Are big group in celebrating freedom of just the house what's one of our lovely friends not tonight where nice couple joined this. Now we have excellent service and the next one time we got everything we ordered I'm not sure who the couple next to us made mad but they certainly did not have the same experience we did I just find it important to note that for some reason. If it had been a reverse situation this would be a different review but personally my experience was five stars had I been them. I've been getting my money back.

Japanese hibachi is as much about the experience as the food and our cook did not disappoint.  In addition to the traditional fire show, he juggled flaming batons and shot fire into the air.  The food was excellent.  The service was good.  I felt like it was money well spent.
Pretty good. It has been quite some time since we have been there. I was to say at least five years. Much better than last time. Pretty busy for a Sunday.

My brother and I celebrated our birthday's at Kobe and they made it really special. Everything was great! The service, chef, food, and of course the birthday cake. I have finally found a Hibachi place that I love in Austin.

This was my 1st time there. So very good. I got the Veggie Wrap with a Power.Slaw side. Wish they had cold green tea but water worked well. The staff there are very friendly and helpful. My husband was very happy at how great his soda was. So many places seem to weaken their sodas 
Will definitely be back. Thanks Orange Clover for the great food and service! You have a new fan.

The lunch menu had a nice variety and I was pleased to find several vegetarian items.  My grilled cheese sandwich and tomato basil soup were both tasty and  filling.  I will definitely be a return customer!
1000% love this place. Been coming here for 3 years. The service is great and the food is better. The owner is super nice and it overall has a fantastic atmosphere!

Fast service, reasonable pricing, friendly staff. A great place for dining in or outdoors. Would have gone with 5 stars, but there was a slight freshness issue with my fruit (that was handled promptly).
So delicious. So fresh! The staff is kind and efficient, and they work hard to keep the flow of the busy lunch crowd managed. Lots of food options for everyone.
I love the jaleno poppers! Arbys has excellent food but just too expensive for a quick bite to eat.
Service is slow! Food is decent! Love the sliders.
I do not think they have ever got my food wrong or ever been bad. And always seems clean. I Recommend them

Roast beef sandwiches aren't all they serve anymore. They also have gyros which are awesome. They will ask if you want Greek, but what they mean to ask is if you want lamb. 

But apparently Americans dont like to eat baby sheep and instead prefer to eat Greeks. I dont get it, but hey, it's probably a market research thing.

They really need to serve schwarma and Poutine.  

Delicious food though, and they have a coke freestyle machine.
It was ok.    Food was good and right.  Service was good bit wish it was a couple minutes faster

While the view is great, our waitress did her utmost while trying to cover too many tables, and our wait to be seated was less than expected on a Friday night - the food was kind of unremarkable or just okay.  Both of the "on tap" items requested weren't actually available, but what was available was good.

Desserts were delicious.

That being said, sends kid friendly and there was a prom crowd in the place that might have been making things difficult for the staff to handle 

The view really is terrific at night.

Nice assortment of pizza and Italian favorites at reasonable prices.  Waitress was very friendly and attentive.  Rocky's has a traditional dinning area, outside patio, and bar area.  The view of the river from the dinning area and patio is great on nice days.

This place has very good food and their plates are very generous. I had to take half of my lunch for later! The staff is very nice! Great service. It is also a really pretty location near the bridge and the Ohio river.

The view is hard to beat one of the best in Louisville. The service was great. The cheese on the pizza was just melted with few toppings and not much flavor. The beer was flat. I asked for a new pizza and the waiter said it didn't look right and had it remade.

For the last four or five years, every time I have been to Rocky's, I've told myself I'm not coming back.  Service has been poor, food has been poor and the place has looked dingy and not so clean. However, I like to support local businesses and I went 1/29/2018 for lunch.  It was the best experience I've had in ages.  I was seated promptly.  The new GM came to with parm and olive oil and to take my drink order.  My drink order was brought promptly by my server along with a loaf of bread for dipping.  I placed my order.  Food arrived promptly and was tastier than I have received in ages at Rocky's.  As I dined I watched the GM and servers clean tables.  Every item was removed, not just pushed around and tables were given a cleaning.  Everyone was cheerful and I felt as if they were indeed glad to have me their.  Keep up the improvement!!

This review is for a visit in March of 2019. I had the cheese burger with bottomless fries and my wife had a burrito serve queso style. Both the burger and the burrito we're very large portions. Our meal was served hot and the server was very attentive to our needs. Like most Mexican restaurants they will bring you chips and salsa before your meal, it's pretty easy to fill up on these at Tumbleweed.

The food was excellent, the prices were a little higher than expected bcuz we went on a Saturday, so there were no specials, but during weekdays, especially at lunchtime, they offer some good deals. The service was decent, our server wasn't overly friendly, but we got our order & drink refills in a very reasonable amount of time. A good experience all around, would definitely go again, just probably at a time & day of the week when specials are on the menu.

Arrived when they opened and the table was filthy. Queso candle was stuck the table with old, dried queso. Asked that it be cleaned, and heard a staff member say "it's just a film it's not dirty." Lady" films aren't crusty. Server was nice enough, but couldn't remember "two cokes" long enough to ring it in without asking again. And no, they weren't busy. Only one other table occupied at that time. Heard wait staff talking about what colors make hair look punk as they colored on a child's menu. Yeah...
 Probably won't be back. Gone in the toilet.
It was good. The customer service from the manager Stacey Blair was phenomenal. You have a great manager with her.
The food was really good! Service was fast and the waitress even pointed out Facebook specials I was not aware of.
Jitter bug

I love Steers and Steers Fish Hoek is a great example of way. The good is good, the service is friendly but they are always very busy so there is a bit of a wait for your food. This does mean that your food is usually freshly made and very tasty!

Really decent burgers, chips were also pretty good. Tasted like the oil was fresh and not repeatedly used like most places. I have to say though, I’m not convinced the flavor in my milkshake came from real limes - colour was a bit off 😋
Always love steers!!!!!! Decent burgers, friendly staff. What more could you want?

Service was quick and seamless.
 And burgers were decent size. No complaints
Good service and quality

Havana belongs on any foodie's "Note to Self" page during visits to Bar Harbor.  Innovative menu for vegans and meat-lovers alike (rare!) and an inviting wine list to boot.  That they remain open most of the year - even off season - adds to our delight in visiting.  Love this place.
Really lovely little restaurant with a friendly staff.  The food was very good and the beer selection decent.  Although they got both of my beer orders wrong I would definitely go back.

Excellent restaurant. Had the fish of the day and by far was the best fish I've ever had. Portion is a little small and wait times can be long, but it is what it is. A few other patrons had the tapas and they looked excellent as well. Would recommend.

Our experience at Havana is second to none. The service was incredible matched only by the food and drinks. Enrique our server was fantastic. I highly recommend the black bean soup, the empanadas and the farmhouse salad, and the Havana martini is tasty.  Thanks!!

Best paella I've ever eaten - generous helping of perfectly-cooked seafood and the saucy rice was just spot on. But everything we had was delicious anyway. The mashed potatoes with coconut that came with one of the daily specials was just... So good...

The wine list is nuts, apparently one of the largest in the region. They have the little notes in the wine menu to help you choose, and we were really happy with the bottle we had.

And of course, the service was excellent. They open at 5pm but it appears that the live music starts a little later.
Incredible concierge staff

This association is know to be a scam , they have recently gotten rid of first residential company that oversees  all residential services such as parking, recieving mail etc, they didnt even give notice to the employees nor did they have a meeting with them about concerns , they made promises about positions and raises and to top things off they had the former business train thete replacements without them even knowing, they had a meeting on valentines day evening and fired everyone the next day without notice , hard working citizens who have been with them 5, 10, 15 years.....

We were looking at condos here until we started talking about the association and the association fees here. I just don't get a good feeling about the homeowners association here. The concrete is crumbling and we can't get a straight answer from anybody about why. We will not be buying a condo here
High living in Buckhead

Historic building
And delightful staff that keep
JC running smooth.

“The City Hall of Jersey City is an elaborate granite and marble structure of mixed Victorian and Classical architecture. It was designed by the architect Lewis H. Broome (1849-1927) and completed in 1896.“
Extremely rude and unhelpful. Asked to be transferred to an employee and they literally told me "I don't know how to help you"

Cultural affairs regular staff is very rude and treats the summer workers as if they don't matter because they're almost expendable but they don't respect them in general as the young ambitious men and women that want to work for the summer
Diversity
The clock itself is cool but the view and surrounding pier is what makes it a good spot! Many families with kids riding scooters and bikes. Couple good restaurants nearby!

One of the places which literally had my hair standing. The New York Skyline that you get to see from here is breathtaking.  Again the place is totally free and easily accessible through public transport. You can just sit there or walk on the boardwalk or hangout with your friends. A dreamy place for me.
Cool spot to visit. Although I did go when it was colder, bundle up it gets cold there. The place has great views of Manhattan. The clock itself is great for photo ops of yourself or your family.

I love this place. The best view of the city from the calmest place in jersey. There are benches to sit and enjoy the view, this place is a great spot to hang around on a summer night! With cool breeze and awesome view, this place is suitable to spend time with family or friends.

It's a Clock. That says Colgate on it. Not much more to say about it.
Although the scenery is nice. You can see parts of the Statue of Liberty and The Freedom tower

Only reason I took away a star is cause you have to pay for parking with admission. Great place for kids (preferably 2+). My son had a blast running around experiencing everything there is to touch. Even my wife and I had a great time learning new things.
This is an amazing place. You can spend the entire day. Lots to do and see. A lit of interactive activities. And any show in the dome is amazing. Bring the kids

Pretty solid science center. There is lots to do for young kids but there is also enough information presented to keep adults entertained. There is quite a good variety of exhibits as well as movie experiences, including a very nice planetarium. It is a bit on the expensive side to get in and any movies aren't included.

Treat it as science center where you take your kids and explore vs. science museum. There are not a lot of contents for adults as it mostly presents interactive exhibition for kids. In the weekend, it will be filled with kids and family. 

The Sherlock Holmes special exhibition is really well designed and cool. Highly recommend!

This is home to the biggest dome in the western hemisphere!
We visited this place on a weekend to catch some astronomy shows, the place itself was not so crowded and the wait time to obtain the show tickets was not that long.
One of the attractive science exhibit was that of the Tesla electricity generation coil, wherein visitors had a chance to experience the fabulous display of electricity in a dark environment which was cool.
We also got a chance to catch 2 planetarium shows one on black holes and other on wonders of night sky. The dome is an absolute delight to the senses, The guides toned down their language to cater to the general public even those who are not very familiar with concepts in astronomy.
Great place to visit on a date night.

This place is awesome! Nothing fancy, but really great bagels. Inexpensive too. Guys are friendly & service was quick. Great breakfast sandwich. 
Had bacon, egg & cheese bagel - huge & yummy. Ordered more bagels to bring home!
A fantastic neighbourhood bagel shop. Everything freshly made to order (so it can take a while!). Really reasonable prices and huge portions of fillings. Good coffee.

Love it - my go to place most mornings in NJ.  Fantastic bagels, relatively inexpensive and a great local business.  Huge range of spreads and the guys are extremely generous in applying them.  

Highly recommend the sausage, egg and cheese on everything.  So so good.

This place is great! great food great people working there as well. very friendly, and quick to get your meal to you.

However in my experience, sometimes they don't fully listen. I've had some of my meals messed or not exactly how i asked for it. 
For instance, i asked would ask for a cup of decaf with 3 sugars and extra cream; they'd give with little cream and no sugar.
sometimes i ask for a thin spread of Olive Pimento and they'd give me a lot.

Otherwise a great place to get a meal.

Fantastic bagels, it was made obvious with the line that had formed. The line moved quickly and efficiently. 

We ended up getting a dozen to bring back down to DC since apparently no one knows how to make a proper bagel down here. The amount of salmon and whitefish on the sandwiches was fantastic

Spontaneously decided to go in here yesterday and boy was I glad I tried it! I didn’t realize it was pretty authentic Dominican restaurant! I was pleasantly surprised. 

I got their beef stew with yellow rice and my friend had the chicken stew with rice and beans! Both items tasted really good! 

The staff was friendly and service was fast! Will definitely be going back to try more of their items!

Great food (love me some mangu and mofongo😋), staff and inexpensive prices. I'm new to the area so I was delighted to find a true Dominican spot in Jersey City. The service is usually fast. The menu changes throughout the day so I recommend calling ahead to get the daily specials.

I go there for lunch every day.  I love this place.  They have a wide variety of selections and the prices are very reasonable.  Also the portions are very big.  You can eat thru dinner.  The ladies are very competent and respectecful. I have nothing better to say.
Very nice employees and food is delish
Great had  a really good chicken noodle soup with white rice to fight of this cold. Price was good too.

I liked the salsa and chips. Our waitress was very distant or busy. The food we ordered was not brought out correctly. Because our waitress was so distant it was hard to get a correction made. Someone else had to go get her. Our drinks ran empty on more than one occasion and we were handed our tab without being offered dessert which I ordered after another waitress noticed me looking around AGAIN. They were not busy by any means we were one of maybe 10 people in the establishment. I usually pop in during lunch. Maybe I will leave it that way from now on. Disapointed on Wednesday@6

Fiesta Grill has become one of my favorites. The staff is friendly, the atmosphere is cozy, to me. The food is really good. I recommend the beef enchiladas, so tasty. Good place to eat either by yourself or with friends and family. They have bigger tables for large groups.

Food was ok, service good. Do NOT offer Military or senior discount. Will NOT visit or become a regular patron to a Restaurant that do not offer these types of discounts,  mainly because a good number of seniors have served in the military so businesses like this one can exist. The least an establishment like this one should do is to show its gratitude to military service members.
Went there for the last time. Hair in to go cup. Food tastes like the kind you get in the frozen food section.
Small town service and feel is great. If you like your Mexican food lightly spiced, you will like this place.
Amazing authentic mexican food... Definitely coming back. After ages, I could devour something that reminded me of roadside Mexican tacos.. definitely will be back.

Taqueria has the best tacos in the area hands down. The delicious lame tacos are a must - and what appears to be freshly made tortilla chips and salsa will tempt you into ruining your appetite - so be careful. The joint itself oozes charm and can get a bit loud at night. But it's worth it for the excellent food and drinks. I swing out here from Hoboken for this place alone.

My husband and I came here on a random whim for date night. We were not expecting what we walked into. We've gone by this corner dozens of times without realizing this place existed. Inside it's tiny, limited first come, first served seating and it's super super casual. No frills, no cheesy Mexican decor...it's just about the food. We were there very late on a Sunday and the place was consistently packed with people flowing in steadily for a seat and for takeout. Everyone in the place was raving about the food for good reason. It's simple but authentic and really good! Price can't be beat either....we ordered A LOT of food and two margaritas (which are very strong!!) and our bill was just about $60...not bad at all. We'll be back. Definitely check this place out. Guac and salsa are outstanding
This location is closer to me and they deliver. I started off by going to the other location, but I'm happy to report that this location lives up to the taqueria standard. Both great!
Very authentic food. We have had take out a few times when visiting the area. The actual restaurant has only a few tables and a small bar. All of our friends love the place.
Great spot, friendly atmosphere, as well as the staff, and Happy hour Specials are on point, as well as the food and drinks. Big ups to Mike, the bartender,  straight up guy, always keeping it💯.
Good cuban food.  Nice drinks.  Several types of Mojitos and Sangria.  All were good.  Great place to hang with friends.
It was great when they were in the old location and it's still a nice spot with great drinks and very good service. Went to celebrate my girls birthday early. Definitely going back.
The place looks amazing and the service was good! The food was very delicious 😊

My coworkers and I threw a surprise bridal shower for our fellow coworker at Hard Grove, and it was the most wonderful experience. Anna helped me to plan the event every step of the way. She was very quick with email responses and very thorough about pricing and packages. She helped to create the perfect, affordable menu for all of us and accommodated our needs of bringing a cake, and decorations. All of the staff was extremely helpful from the moment we walked in. They helped me decorate and asked our preferences of how we wanted to be seated and when the food should come out. The food was absolutely delicious and is so filling! We had an array of appetizers- plantain chips and guacamole, a variety of empanadas, and ham croquettes- all so delicious. We had 2 choices for our main course- rice and chicken or a vegetarian meal. Everyone was very pleased and super full! We also ordered drinks to the table and the most popular drink seemed to be the pitchers of sangria. Great price and a great amount of sangria. The music and atmosphere was so fun. The waiters were always smiling, taking pictures for us, and seemed to be having fun as well.  We all had a wonderful night and we are so thankful for the hospitality and delicious food we had at Hard Grove. We will all be back very soon! 😊

Wow! What a gem on 4th. Went with a group of friends for brunch on a recommendation and was not disappointed. Before I get ahead of myself, reservations are extremely recommended on Friday, Saturday, Sunday. With that being said you want to make one here. Decor is fantastic, many handcrafted pieces. Rustic yet elegant. Our server Roger was quick, witty and charming. Service was speedy, never felt rushed. We ordered a few different items and all were delicious. Their drink of the day was delightful! We also tried all the desserts on the brunch menu -‘cause why not?!- and surprise! Scrumptious! We enjoyed this place so much we have all decided to make this our next date night spot. Thank you for the great food and experience!

Good food, but a bit overpriced. We really liked the mushroom appetizer (I think it was a special of the day). The duck was also very good. The seafood special was OK. The flourless chocolate cake was very rich and good with the ice cream, but we needed more ice cream. We brought half home and enjoyed it with more ice cream.

Now that the menu is limited if you are vegetarian.
Such a lovely place for the Valentine’s Day dinner. Super delicious food and fun live music, made my day! Will be back for sure!

the overall vibe of this restaurant is amazing! the exposed brick- live music on Thursday's and the escargot is the best i've ever had... definitely a place you should check out!! Roger was an awesome waiter too :)

Consistently great food and service...Been here 4-5 times in the past year...The duck and lamb shank are always amazing... Also, the goat special is great when offered..Check out the signature cocktails and don't forget dessert...

Great food, hostess was gorgeous and very nice. This place is for the milder curry lovers and great if you are bringing people to try Indian for the first time. However....my truck got booted and the ransom was 60 bucks. Note...DO NO PARK ON THE MCDONALD'S SIDE OF THE RESTAURANT.

The atmosphere is beautiful.  We loved the sauces, rice, and naan but the chicken and lamb were too tough and didn't taste very good.  They were short-staffed the night we went but our waitress was nice.

The standard Indian fare can be found here, with some very tasty additions.  I was very impressed with the coconut tomato soup - I'll definitely be coming back for more!  The thalis are large, but not quite as diverse as one can find elsewhere.

Great buffet style Indian restaurant. Loved the vegetarian options. The chicken curry was a little sweet, but you get fresh naan delivered to your table and masala tea on the buffet as well. I will definitely be back here! The atmosphere is cozy and inviting; the chairs are great! It's like being in a friend's living room. A must for lunch. :)

Just went their to lunch today. It was a buffet for 10$ (tip+tax included) and I have to say the food was just delicious. Definitely the best Indian restaurant I ever tried in Abq. Everything was so tasteful and there was a great variety of vegetarian food (even if the best was the chicken). Service was very good; but I gotta say for a buffet you dont expect much. Our waitress was so nice, she came to ask several times if everything was fine and even gave us a bunch of naan bread to eat later on the day.

Recommended 100% 

Did not go for dinner yet, so no idea about the menu/price/service, but the lunch was so good that I'm sure you can find amazingly good tasting food.

Why two stars? This is truly an important and fascinating place to visit.  I would even say a must visit if in Jerusalen. However, the English guided tour we had was very poor as far as knowledge of the sites and history as well as in terms of language proficiency.

All of my life I have heard stories from the Bible and somehow thought all of those places would take days or weeks to walk to. It is interesting how close the Mount of Olives,  Gethsemane, Galgotha and other places are. My wife and I felt completely safe walking to and around the Old City as well as strolling around Jerusalem.

This place is incredible! If you love Biblical history and want to walk through time, this is the place to go! Asher was an awesome guide. His background in archeology and great knowledge of the Bible, really made it a memorable event!

Fascinating excavation of the ancient city of Jerusalem. We took the three hour guided tour with tour guide Yossi. Although it is possible to explore the area on your own, the perspective of a knowledgeable tour guide is invaluable. Although we elected to take the dry route through the water tunnels, two members of our group went through the water. If you do this you must bring good sneakers or boots and remember that at the beginning the water is 70cm deep.
Fascinating place! Going into Hezekiah tunnel is a an awesome historical experience. I highly recommend to visit it.

Just two small rooms,one for men and the other for women! A man asking for money which goes for charity...he gave me a candle and wrote my name on a piece of paper and putt it inside the tomb for good luck...
the 17th Prophet David PBUH, part of pilgrim.  Rich of Culture such as building and atmosphere
Amazing to be able just to walk in and oray at such a significant pkace. Apparently I'm aroind 106 generations from him!
Great spiritual location to pray.

King David's Tomb is a synagouge (Jewish Place of Prayer) located on Mt. Zion next to Diaspora Yeshiva. It is located above the entrance to the burial cave complex of King David and it leads to his tomb.
 The entrance to the tomb itself is sealed by a monument stone, but it is open to the public. Keep in mind thay while any private individual may pray there GROUP  services of other faiths are prohibited by law.
  Please be respectful of the holiness of this place and cover your head at all times.
This is the house of Caiaphas. An amazing historical place to see. You really get a vivid idea of the night Jesus had in front of the High Priest before  standing before Pilot.

The Church of the cockroach is more than wonderful because you will discover in the cellar how they took the Lord Jesus Christ to this place and go down with the rope and leave him for days without food or eating until they took him to trial at Pilate. And this is what we did not know about him. In this place, I advise you to visit this church because it deserves to discover the truth of the place, and the church is more than wonderful.

This church is the place of Caiaphas the High Priest in the New Testament. He played a major role in the arrest and torture of Jesus, and while the church is impressive...even more staggering is the 3 levels of prison cellars underneath where they tortured Jesus. It is dark, somber and very thought provoking. 

I suggest reading Psalm 88 while you are here to get a glimpse of what Jesus felt while he was in this place.

Place where Jesus spent his last night before being cruxified. Spending some time in the lowest dungeon of the high priest Caiaphas' palace is a sombering thought while meditating on Psalm 88. I actually sat down in the small niche under the stairs, experiencing the dampness and cold...

Amazing experience. You see the steps Jesus took after his arrest. You see the spot where Peter denied Christ in the courtyard. You see the cell where he was held under the house of Caiphas. Really moving. Do not miss!

Best  experience.   Peace and spiritual  uplift ment.  Every Muslim must visit even if it's once in a lifetime

Mosque located within the same plaza as the dome of the rock. It is a worship place so you must be respectful all the time. The place can also be accessed through the access point at the Dung gate. No entrance fee, however check the entrance times that are usually two, one in the morning and one in the afternoon. Closed on  Fridays.

The Tomb of the Virgin Mary is situated near the Church of All Nations and the Garden of Gethsemane. Visiting the tomb is a memorable experience: Visitors must go deep underground, down a staircase that was carved in the rock during the twelfth century. Immediately surrounding is a sparkling array of iconography, hanging from the ceiling and decorating the cave walls. Medieval art, including a painting of the Madonna and Child, adorn this sanctuary.
The crypt is sheltered within a barrier, so that a visitor must bend forward in order to enter. This forces people to bow and thereby demonstrate their respect for the sanctity of the site. The tomb has been dated as early as the first century. A church was built above the tomb during the same period that Constantine built the Church of the Holy Sepulchre, where some Catholics believe the tomb of Jesus is located. Most Christians believe that Mary was resurrected after her death.

The Church of St. John the Baptist is one of the oldest churches in Jerusalem, with roots dating back to the mid 5th century. Historically, it has been a Mosque as well as a hospice during the Crusader period. However, presently it is a Greek Orthodox church. 

The exterior of the building is being restored at present, meaning it can't be accessed at Muristan. However, if you walk back to Christian Quarter Road, you'll find a small alleyway leading to the courtyard where the church can be entered and visited. You will notice a small sign which states that the church remains open from 9am to 5pm daily but closed on Sundays. 

Inside you will find darkly lit rooms decorated in early Christian and Greek Orthodox manner. Attractive chandeliers hang from a ceiling and there are nicely painted images to see. Heavily gilded iconostasis and entire walls lined with beautiful iconic images can be seen. The interior is small and can be conveniently enjoyed in 5-10 minutes if you are short on time. 

Overall, The Church of St. John the Baptist is an interesting ancient church that many seem to skip or not know about. We really enjoyed finding and visiting while sightseeing in the Christian Quarter and would gladly return if we were to visit the city again.

The Monastery of the Flagellation is an important attraction along the Via Dolorosa in the Muslim Quarter of Jerusalem. This is the location where is is believed that Jesus was flogged by the Roman soldiers. Opening hours are from 9-1pm and 4-6pm daily. 

Here you can find a pleasant but small courtyard flanked by two chapels. The Chapel of the Condemnation is a 20th century chapel built upon the grounds of medieval period chapel. The interior is that of a small seating area with nice stained glass windows. 

Across the courtyard is a second Chapel of the Flagellation, which was originally built during the Crusader period and then restored by Italian architect Antonio Barluzzi in 1929. Here you can see a nice altar with an image of Christ being led beside the cross. 

Between the two chapels is a small archaeological museum called Terra Sancta Museum. We didn't have time to visit but this might be of interest to some. They have a website online if you want to know more about what can be experienced here. 

Overall, we found the Monastery of Flagellation to be a nice addition to the various attractions along Via Dolorosa. Its worth a visit if you plan to trace the steps of Jesus and visit the 14 stations along this street.

Невелика синагога «Бейт-Тфіла Біньямін» була збудована 1923 року на пожертвування родини Біньяміна Шапіро. 1938 року на будинку було встановлено меморіальну дошку з написом, виконаним єврейськими літерами німецькою мовою (не їдишем). Це свідчить про те, наскільки чернівецькі євреї були асимільовані в німецькомовну культуру навіть у період румунського правління, яке чинило опір німецькому культурному впливу. В період з 1959 по 1994 рр. вона була єдиною діючою синагогою в місті. Особливу цінність становлять її внутрішні розписи, виконані невідомим чернівецьким художником. Розписи вкривають практично весь внутрішній простір приміщення. За своєю самобутністю та художнім рівнем ці розписи є визначним зразком релігійної єврейської творчості Східної Європи.

Not all lift operators are created equal; and, if only going round-trip, once, it's an expensive ride! Those two things being said, as a local, I love the tram. The views are stellar and it's a wonderful experience to see Juneau from new heights without hiking up a mountain on one's own to do so.

Most of the tramway 🚡 operators are knowledgeable, out-going, and enjoy what they do. I have yet to meet an employee working the tram that I didn't like! Be aware that the tram, as it's being docked at the top, does slow down and rock gently back and forth prior to it lodging firmly into place for your safe exit on the top of Mount Roberts. If you have a fear of heights, the rocking motion may make you uneasy; and, it's important to note, the tram does have you riding above treetops. If afraid of heights, look out and not down! The lift takes about 5 minutes to go up and 5 minutes to go back down and is made available for either direction within reasonably spaced, short intervals. Once off-loaded, at the top of Mount Roberts, take your time to enjoy the Nature Center, the Gift Shop, Grab a Bite to Eat, and find your way to Father Brown's Cross for Amazing, Awe-inspiring Views that seem like movie back-drops but are perfectly real; a place where time stands still. 

What goes up, must come down; thankfully, a tram like the one in Juneau is safe, secure, and smooth. It seems to glide as it brings you back down to earth. It's a brilliant contraption that's well maintained and kept clean. If a tourist, the expensive, round-trip ticket is worth the cost for a once in a lifetime experience like none other. If a local, the season pass would be a good thing to nab as it'll save you money and allow you to travel, by tram, as often as you'd like. 😊
